    <title type="html"><![CDATA[kinoko-gohan]]></title>
    <link href="http://pelupessy.github.io/blog/2017/07/17/kinoko-gohan/"/>
    <updated>2017-07-17T18:55:00+09:00</updated>
    <id>http://pelupessy.github.io/blog/2017/07/17/kinoko-gohan</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p><strong>英語で:</strong> As mentioned before, rice is the staple of the Japanese diet. Once one <a href="http://www.justhungry.com/handbook/cooking-courses/japanese-cooking-101-lesson-2-great-japanese-rice">knows the basics of cooking it</a>, one can add some extras.</p>

<p><strong>Japanese:</strong> きのこごはんつくりました。</p>

<p><a href="https://photos.smugmug.com/photos/i-VrRvsG8/0/18dbe7f6/X3/i-VrRvsG8-X3.jpg"><img class="center" src="https://photos.smugmug.com/photos/i-VrRvsG8/0/18dbe7f6/XL/i-VrRvsG8-XL.jpg"></a></p>

<p><a href="https://photos.smugmug.com/photos/i-QXmGjkp/0/78def97f/X3/i-QXmGjkp-X3.jpg"><img class="center" src="https://photos.smugmug.com/photos/i-QXmGjkp/0/78def97f/XL/i-QXmGjkp-XL.jpg"></a></p>

<p>だし</p>

<p>The day before, add <em>konbu</em> (kelp) and dried mushrooms to water and leave in the refrigerator to create a <em>dashi</em>.</p>

<!-- more -->


<p><a href="https://photos.smugmug.com/photos/i-pvP66Jq/0/59fae2c9/X3/i-pvP66Jq-X3.jpg"><img class="center" src="https://photos.smugmug.com/photos/i-pvP66Jq/0/59fae2c9/XL/i-pvP66Jq-XL.jpg"></a></p>

<p><em>honmirin</em>, soy-sause, dashi.</p>

<p><a href="https://photos.smugmug.com/photos/i-P84nqhH/0/75e8679b/X3/i-P84nqhH-X3.jpg"><img class="center" src="https://photos.smugmug.com/photos/i-P84nqhH/0/75e8679b/XL/i-P84nqhH-XL.jpg"></a></p>

<p>Chop, chop.</p>

<p><a href="https://photos.smugmug.com/photos/i-BfvBV4F/0/45a47123/X3/i-BfvBV4F-X3.jpg"><img class="center" src="https://photos.smugmug.com/photos/i-BfvBV4F/0/45a47123/XL/i-BfvBV4F-XL.jpg"></a></p>

<p><a href="https://photos.smugmug.com/photos/i-4S67GNg/0/ad4b90d9/X3/i-4S67GNg-X3.jpg"><img class="center" src="https://photos.smugmug.com/photos/i-4S67GNg/0/ad4b90d9/XL/i-4S67GNg-XL.jpg"></a></p>

<p>For two portions, add the <em>honmirin</em> and soy-sause to taste to one cup of (cleaned) rice, about one table spoon each. Fill with <em>dashi</em> up to the amount indicated by the rice cooker or recipe.</p>

<p><a href="https://photos.smugmug.com/photos/i-rZfwSxz/0/b21ff150/X3/i-rZfwSxz-X3.jpg"><img class="center" src="https://photos.smugmug.com/photos/i-rZfwSxz/0/b21ff150/XL/i-rZfwSxz-XL.jpg"></a></p>

<p><a href="https://photos.smugmug.com/photos/i-wJbKDdz/0/dfe64f65/X3/i-wJbKDdz-X3.jpg"><img class="center" src="https://photos.smugmug.com/photos/i-wJbKDdz/0/dfe64f65/XL/i-wJbKDdz-XL.jpg"></a></p>

<p>Add mushrooms, both the chopped ones and some fresh ones.</p>

<p><a href="https://photos.smugmug.com/photos/i-pWzbhkd/0/02cd2d61/X3/i-pWzbhkd-X3.jpg"><img class="center" src="https://photos.smugmug.com/photos/i-pWzbhkd/0/02cd2d61/XL/i-pWzbhkd-XL.jpg"></a></p>

<p>Press the red button or follow the plain rice recipe as usual.</p>

<p><a href="ghttps://photos.smugmug.com/photos/i-KR69MpJ/0/83cabb26/X3/i-KR69MpJ-X3.jpg"><img class="center" src="https://photos.smugmug.com/photos/i-KR69MpJ/0/83cabb26/XL/i-KR69MpJ-XL.jpg"></a></p>

<p>Mix before serving.</p>

<p><a href="https://photos.smugmug.com/photos/i-sFRGwVW/0/6ccce841/X3/i-sFRGwVW-X3.jpg"><img class="center" src="https://photos.smugmug.com/photos/i-sFRGwVW/0/6ccce841/XL/i-sFRGwVW-XL.jpg"></a></p>

<p>Serve and eat.</p>
]]></content>
